  "description": {
    "lang": "eng",
    "value": "JFrog Artifactory before 7.29.3 and 6.23.38, is vulnerable to Broken Access Control, a low-privileged user is able to delete other known users OAuth token, which will force a reauthentication on an active session or in the next UI session.\n\nReason for inclusion in AVID: CVE-2021-45074 describes a broken access control vulnerability in JFrog Artifactory affecting OAuth tokens; Artifactory is a widely-used artifact/repository tool in software supply chains and ML pipelines, so this is a software supply chain vulnerability relevant to general-purpose AI systems; it is a security vulnerability with clear evidence (CVE entry, CVSS details, references)."
  },
